HEADWORD: Hurly
<hw>Hur"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hurler</ets> to howl.]</ety> <def>Noise; confusion;
uproar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That, with the <qex>hurly</qex>, death itself awakes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurly-burly</ent>⟦br⟧
